      <p> Turner JR. Editor’s commentary: ethics in clinical research. <italic>Drug Information Journal</italic>. 2012;46(2):155-157. (Original doi: 10.1177/0092861512438841)</p>
      <p>In the Editor’s Commentary for the March 2012 issue, the bold text in the sentence below (from page 156, left column) is incorrect:</p>
      <p> Since power is calculated as (1 – β), the choice of <bold>β = 1</bold> would yield a power of 0.90, typically written as 90%.</p>
      <p>The corrected text reads:</p>
      <p> Since power is calculated as (1 – β), the choice of <bold>β = 0.10</bold> would yield a power of 0.90, typically written as 90%.</p>
